**File and Line Number:** `settings.js`, Line 9
**Description:** 
The code uses `_.merge({}, defaults, req.body)` to combine user-supplied input from `req.body` into a settings object. In older or vulnerable versions of `lodash`, the `merge` function recursively merges properties without validating the keys. An attacker can send a JSON payload containing the `__proto__` property (e.g., `{"__proto__": {"isAdmin": true}}`). Because `merge` follows the prototype chain, this will inject the `isAdmin` property into the base `Object.prototype`. Since almost all objects in JavaScript inherit from this prototype, every object in the application will now possess the `isAdmin: true` property, potentially leading to privilege escalation or Denial of Service (DoS).

